The paper deals with algorithms for optimal partitions in tree metrics, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses an extension of the method to bounded treewidth graphs, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves optimization problems, which could be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
